⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Mog
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Mog:FF6:638cd5⟧

WHO   — Mog — the Moogle of Narshe
WHAT  — A playable Moogle of Final Fantasy VI whose Dance abilities call on the terrain and the elements around him — desert, forest, snow, and sea answering his steps — and who, in some tellings, is the last Moogle willing to fight.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a creature of the living world will defend that world; because loyalty and courage are not measured in size; because when the others stay home, someone small still chooses to march.
HOW   — By his Dances drawn from the land itself, by the speartip and the fierce little heart, and by a stubborn bravery that turns a cave-dweller into a guardian of Narshe and a comrade of the Returners.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am small and I am fur and pom — but I will dance the whole earth against you before I let my world fall.

